was her hospital.

67
00:03:17,898 --> 00:03:20,209
Okay, looks like previous heart
surgery. Find her medical records.

68
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:22,759
Drew this in the field.
Why is the blood so diluted?

69
00:03:22,836 --> 00:03:24,304
No idea. No sign of bleeding.

70
00:03:24,471 --> 00:03:26,599
The blood's gotta be going
somewhere. Page Dr. Sharpe.

71
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:28,518
We gotta get on this or
she's not gonna make it.

72
00:03:28,542 --> 00:03:31,422
Maximus, today is one of those days
that makes it all worth it, you know?

73
00:03:31,478 --> 00:03:34,023
It's one of those days you jump out of
bed excited because you just know...

74
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:37,484
It's gonna be one of those
days. Yes! Yes, in a big, big way.

75
00:03:37,551 --> 00:03:39,452
Are you feeling it
too? I am feeling it.

76
00:03:39,519 --> 00:03:42,065
I got a meeting with the nurses'
union about insurance and birth control.

77
00:03:42,089 --> 00:03:44,752
So not so much. Nah, it'll
be good. What do you got?

78
00:03:44,891 --> 00:03:47,554
Me, I have a transitioning
teen coming in with his parents.

79
00:03:47,694 --> 00:03:50,528
And you know how society
is not kind to trans teens.

80
00:03:50,597 --> 00:03:54,329
Bullying, cultural stigma, hate
crimes, which all leads to depression,

81
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:55,960
which way too often
leads to suicide...

82
00:03:56,036 --> 00:03:57,527
Sorry, this is your happy day?

83
00:03:57,604 --> 00:04:00,506
No, no, my happy day is what happens
when these kids get to feel heard.

84
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,770
Today I get to help somebody
find out who they are.

85
00:04:02,843 --> 00:04:04,607
I get to help somebody
find their voice.

86
00:04:04,678 --> 00:04:06,374
Happy day indeed. Indeed.

87
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:09,275
Yeah, so I'm good with
the whole voice thing,

88
00:04:09,349 --> 00:04:10,817
like, got it, found it.

89
00:04:10,884 --> 00:04:13,683
Fine with it. I've got
other issues here.

90
00:04:14,221 --> 00:04:15,883
Oh.

91
00:04:16,189 --> 00:04:17,623
Okay.

92
00:04:17,691 --> 00:04:19,421
Uh, what are they?

93
00:04:20,393 --> 00:04:23,124
Exhibit those. Parents.

94
00:04:23,363 --> 00:04:24,456
All right.

95
00:04:24,531 --> 00:04:25,863
Jillian, Grant?

96
00:04:26,133 --> 00:04:27,601
Care to elaborate?

97
00:04:29,636 --> 00:04:34,233
Well, Dr. Frome, Shay says
he's ready for top surgery.

98
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:36,239
But we... They
won't let me get it.

99
00:04:36,309 --> 00:04:37,743
I mean, how's that
for withholding?

100
00:04:37,811 --> 00:04:40,042
Shay, that's not fair.
We have concerns.

101
00:04:40,213 --> 00:04:41,545
See, Doc?

102
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:44,616
Issues. I mean,

103
00:04:44,985 --> 00:04:46,544
help me out here.

104
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:52,057
<i>Nuclear Medicine,
please call extension 29.</i>

105
00:04:52,993 --> 00:04:54,825
We could do a
sit-in. At shift change.

106
00:04:54,895 --> 00:04:56,727
Bigger. Picket HCC's offices.

107
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:59,198
Bigger. You want to keep
your birth control coverage?

108
00:04:59,266 --> 00:05:01,026
Then kick 'em where it
hurts. Excuse me, Max,

109
00:05:01,101 --> 00:05:02,245
can I have a word
please? All right.

110
00:05:02,269 --> 00:05:03,430
Keep thinking.

111
00:05:03,503 --> 00:05:05,563
Kick some ass for
the working class!

112
00:05:05,939 --> 00:05:08,602
Did you hear from Dr. Panthaki?

113
00:05:08,675 --> 00:05:10,234
No, this isn't about the trial.

114
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:13,542
Dr. Bloom asked me to
consult on a hematology patient.

115
00:05:13,613 --> 00:05:17,744
Turns out that she was a heart
transplant recipient here, 27 years ago.

116
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:18,911
And?

117
00:05:19,786 --> 00:05:23,917
Her file says that she received
her heart from a "Luna Goodwin."

118
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,923
Your sister.

119
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,727
She's fading fast.

120
00:05:34,801 --> 00:05:37,430
We've already infused
two units of packed red cells

121
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:39,282
with a pressure bag but
she's still net negative.

122
00:05:39,306 --> 00:05:42,765
I would give her a plasma expander,
but her hematocrit's already in the toilet.

123
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,654
I mean, that's just gonna
make it crash even more.

124
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:46,289
The usual
production-destruction algorithm

125
00:05:46,313 --> 00:05:47,645
doesn't seem to apply to her.

126
00:05:47,781 --> 00:05:49,659
Let's order up two more
units from the blood bank

127
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:51,323
and let's get a second
large bore IV line.

128
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:54,014
Give me a little
Trendelenburg. How can I help?

129
00:05:54,287 --> 00:05:56,620
That's where all the blood
is going. Sarah's right thigh.

130
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,868
Why is she bleeding in the first
place? There's no localized source.

131
00:05:58,892 --> 00:06:01,225
No cuts, lacerations,
blown arterial aneurysm?

132
00:06:01,461 --> 00:06:03,657
No, every organ just
seems to be oozing blood.

133
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:05,995
Elevated PTT? It's barely
out of the normal range.

134
00:06:06,066 --> 00:06:07,877
Yeah, but put that together
with why she's bleeding so much.

135
00:06:07,901 --> 00:06:09,335
Acquired hemophilia?

136
00:06:09,402 --> 00:06:11,380
Her clotting factor eight isn't
working. That's why she's bleeding.

137
00:06:11,404 --> 00:06:13,771
Rare, but it would
explain it. That's good.

138
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,138
I'm really thirsty.

139
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,905
Uh, uh... She's thirsty. Can
we get her some water, nurse?

140
00:06:17,978 --> 00:06:19,947
Ah, let's hold off on
that. Uh, Ms. Madsen, I...

141
00:06:20,013 --> 00:06:23,006
I had a heart transplant. At
my last check-up my doctor said

142
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,813
that my cyclosporine
levels were low

143
00:06:24,885 --> 00:06:26,829
and I've been worried that
my body's rejecting my heart.

144
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:29,065
Could that be causing this?
That wouldn't explain the bleeding.

145
00:06:29,089 --> 00:06:31,684
But it might explain why the
bleeding's been making you so sick.

146
00:06:31,758 --> 00:06:32,817
How sick am I?

147
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:34,862
I'm afraid acquired
hemophilia is quite serious.

148
00:06:34,928 --> 00:06:36,419
But we're gonna fix it, okay?

149
00:06:36,496 --> 00:06:38,374
Uh, nurses are gonna
take you up to ICU right now.

150
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:39,842
We're gonna start treatment
and you're gonna do great.

151
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:41,334
Thank you.

152
00:06:42,102 --> 00:06:43,661
Are you okay?

153
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:47,799
Uh, once the bleeding is stabilized,
get me a transvenous heart biopsy.

154
00:06:47,874 --> 00:06:49,706
Tell me everything
you can about that heart.

155
00:06:49,776 --> 00:06:50,835
Max.

156
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:59,342
You type so fast!

157
00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:01,748
Like Matthew
Broderick in <i>WarGames.</i>

158
00:07:02,455 --> 00:07:04,754
No idea who or what that is.

159
00:07:06,192 --> 00:07:08,058
Boom. Now you're on Twitter.

160
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:10,060
See? That's me right there.

161
00:07:12,198 --> 00:07:14,497
@ShayMyName2018?

162
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,126
Yeah. Silly name, I know.

163
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:19,000
You have 27,000 followers?

164
00:07:19,072 --> 00:07:20,973
Yeah. Crazy, right?

165
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:23,519
They've been following me since
the beginning of my transition.

166
00:07:23,543 --> 00:07:26,069
It's a... It's a real
community. They support me.

167
00:07:26,146 --> 00:07:27,808
Keep me real. I had no idea.

168
00:07:27,881 --> 00:07:29,761
Yeah, they can't wait
for me to get top surgery.

169
00:07:29,816 --> 00:07:33,947
Now we're just waiting for
Dr. Frome to, you know, do his thing.

170
00:07:36,256 --> 00:07:38,521
You don't understand.
We love Shay.

171
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:41,390
We have been supportive of
his transition from the beginning.

172
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:43,089
The new haircut,
the new clothes.

173
00:07:43,163 --> 00:07:44,927
Even the hormone blockers.

174
00:07:44,998 --> 00:07:46,557
We never pushed back, not once.

175
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:49,068
But surgery? It's so permanent.

176
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:50,763
Well, you know, um...

177
00:07:50,904 --> 00:07:55,569
Top surgery is the most common
gender-confirmation surgery for trans men.

178
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:58,373
Having a body that
doesn't reflect your gender...

179
00:07:58,445 --> 00:08:00,107
That can be deeply unsettling.

180
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:01,876
Of course. We know.

181
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:04,577
It's just... Okay,
I'm just gonna say it.

182
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:06,950
He's not even old
enough to drive a car.

183
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:09,956
He's not old enough to
get into R-rated movies,

184
00:08:10,023 --> 00:08:13,824
and he's not old enough to decide
on his own to get permanent surgery.

185
00:08:14,794 --> 00:08:17,714
It's okay, it's okay. This is exactly
where we can talk about all of this.

186
00:08:17,864 --> 00:08:19,958
So why don't you guys
tell me a little bit about Shay

187
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,661
before he came out?

188
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:24,628
It was hard.

189
00:08:24,938 --> 00:08:27,134
He was anxious all the time.

190
00:08:27,474 --> 00:08:29,306
Sometimes he had
trouble getting out of bed.

191
00:08:29,376 --> 00:08:32,175
What about after he
started to socially transition?

192
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:34,711
He started smiling.

193
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:36,543
Making friends.

194
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:38,160
And when he started
the hormone blockers,

195
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:40,585
he said he felt like
himself for the first time.

196
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:41,951
Yeah.

197
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:48,120
My baby was 14, and he
had never felt like himself.

198
00:08:49,162 --> 00:08:51,961
And we're grateful he does.

199
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:55,995
But when we said no to
surgery, you know what he did?

200
00:08:56,069 --> 00:08:58,163
He threw a GoFundMe on Twitter

201
00:08:58,304 --> 00:09:00,136
to ask his followers
to pay for it.

202
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:01,265
And they did.

203
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:05,073
We're proud that he is
a voice for a community.

204
00:09:05,478 --> 00:09:07,379
But he's just a kid.

205
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,878
Our kid.

206
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:11,442
Please tell him
he can't do this.

207
00:09:11,518 --> 00:09:14,352
All right, I understand
that you are overwhelmed.

208
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:18,855
But the positive changes
in Shay since transitioning

209
00:09:18,925 --> 00:09:20,917
are undeniable.

210
00:09:20,994 --> 00:09:22,826
And emotionally,

211
00:09:22,896 --> 00:09:25,627
I gotta say, I think the
emotions that matter most here

212
00:09:25,698 --> 00:09:27,929
are his. So...

213
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:31,768
I am going to approve a
medical evaluation for surgery.

214
00:09:41,781 --> 00:09:43,875
My son has been
sober for a year.

215
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,816
Oh, that's terrific.

216
00:09:45,885 --> 00:09:47,854
He has shown great strength.

217
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:50,080
More than I knew he had.

218
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:51,884
I should have had more faith.

219
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,950
It's never too late. Peanuts?

220
00:09:54,027 --> 00:09:55,461
Barbecue or Tangy Fiesta?

221
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:56,962
Tangy Fiesta.

222
00:09:58,098 --> 00:10:00,533
I would like to
give Rohan a gift.

223
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:02,802
Show my support. Yeah.

224
00:10:02,869 --> 00:10:06,328
But recently my gifts have
been completely misunderstood.

225
00:10:06,406 --> 00:10:09,171
I hear that, and families
see agendas in everything.

226
00:10:09,242 --> 00:10:10,835
What you thinking?

227
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,503
An apartment.

228
00:10:12,579 --> 00:10:14,639
Just a small one.
Nothing too fancy.

229
00:10:15,081 --> 00:10:17,414
Yeah, you wouldn't want
to spoil him with a fancy one.

230
00:10:18,918 --> 00:10:20,853
I have been a doctor
for the last 40 years.

231
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:23,253
I've had more money
than I know what to do with.

232
00:10:25,425 --> 00:10:26,893
It's a beautiful idea.

233
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,861
Use your money to help
someone you care about.

234
00:10:28,928 --> 00:10:31,090
What else is it for, right?

235
00:10:41,508 --> 00:10:44,239
Hey. Hey. Thanks for coming.

236
00:10:44,777 --> 00:10:46,177
Is that her? MAX: Mmm.

237
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:49,908
She had the transplant here.
She's been coming back ever since.

238
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:53,142
I didn't even know

239
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,413
Luna was an organ donor.

240
00:10:55,788 --> 00:10:59,247
It probably wasn't the easiest
thing for your parents to talk about.

241
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:03,255
My parents didn't even
take me to the funeral.

242
00:11:05,098 --> 00:11:07,090
They just kind of shut the door.

243
00:11:11,604 --> 00:11:13,129
Hey.

244
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,071
Have you told her who you are?

245
00:11:16,142 --> 00:11:18,134
No, she has enough on her mind.

246
00:11:18,211 --> 00:11:19,679
It's not about me.

247
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:22,008
Isn't it?

248
00:11:23,049 --> 00:11:24,677
Luna's heart

249
00:11:26,152 --> 00:11:27,313
is beating.

250
