start to bleed again.

302
00:14:08,781 --> 00:14:12,548
Which we won't let happen. I'll be
doing a blood test called the PTT.

303
00:14:12,618 --> 00:14:15,611
I'll be drawing it from the
central line every 20 minutes,

304
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:19,090
and then based on the results,
I will adjust the rate of infusion.

305
00:14:19,158 --> 00:14:20,238
Will that take a long time?

306
00:14:20,293 --> 00:14:22,159
Yes, it will. Hopefully not.

307
00:14:24,330 --> 00:14:27,323
It's not something that
we can definitively know.

308
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,336
Yeah, but however
long it may take,

309
00:14:30,403 --> 00:14:32,804
I will be here by your side

310
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,170
night and day

311
00:14:34,674 --> 00:14:36,267
till we get it right.

312
00:14:36,342 --> 00:14:37,674
Why me?

313
00:14:37,744 --> 00:14:39,042
Excuse me?

314
00:14:39,245 --> 00:14:43,273
Well, um, you're the Medical
Director of the entire hospital.

315
00:14:43,349 --> 00:14:46,649
You're dropping
everything for me, Dr., uh...

316
00:14:46,919 --> 00:14:49,218
Uh... Goodwin, Max.

317
00:14:50,256 --> 00:14:51,315
Um...

318
00:14:52,492 --> 00:14:54,154
Just an interesting case.

319
00:14:54,394 --> 00:14:57,193
Dr. Goodwin, Dr. Sharpe.
Could I have a minute?

320
00:14:57,263 --> 00:14:58,697
Excuse us.

321
00:15:04,337 --> 00:15:06,932
I, uh, got the results
from Sarah's heart biopsy.

322
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:10,943
The heart muscle showed both
fibrosis and T-lymphocyte infiltration.

323
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:12,501
It's Grade 4.

324
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:14,103
Well, it doesn't get much worse.

325
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:15,705
Okay, so we up the
cyclosporine dose.

326
00:15:16,082 --> 00:15:17,326
Why would we...
If we up the dose

327
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:19,728
