That's out of the question.

329
00:15:21,087 --> 00:15:23,955
Look, the stress from Sarah's
hemophilia has ravaged her heart.

330
00:15:24,023 --> 00:15:26,822
So un-ravage it. I gave you a
whole cardio department, use it,

331
00:15:26,893 --> 00:15:29,385
because we sure as hell
aren't going to just sit here

332
00:15:29,462 --> 00:15:30,589
while... What? Max.

333
00:15:32,198 --> 00:15:34,531
Luna's heart is dying.

334
00:15:36,803 --> 00:15:37,896
It's gone.

335
00:15:40,139 --> 00:15:41,869
That's my sister's heart.

336
00:15:43,643 --> 00:15:45,236
We have to save it.

337
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:47,075
No.

338
00:15:47,580 --> 00:15:49,947
We have to save Sarah.

339
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,095
And the only thing that's
gonna do that is a new heart.

340
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:55,714
Because the old
one is out of time.

341
00:16:05,031 --> 00:16:07,330
The waiting list for heart
transplants isn't short,

342
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,835
but the good news
is you're at the top.

343
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:12,438
And priority goes to
the most severe cases

344
00:16:12,505 --> 00:16:14,167
that can withstand a transplant.

345
00:16:14,407 --> 00:16:17,571
Wow. That's, uh, great. Also...

346
00:16:18,177 --> 00:16:19,543
Totally terrifying.

347
00:16:19,612 --> 00:16:21,410
Right. So...

348
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:22,574
OTF gets us a heart,

349
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,674
we fix the hemophilia

350
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:25,945
and you walk out of here.

351
00:16:26,018 --> 00:16:27,748
That's the plan.
I like the plan.

352
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,448
Me too, so...

353
00:16:29,522 --> 00:16:30,683
Hang in there.

354
00:16:30,756 --> 00:16:31,951
Question.

355
00:16:32,024 --> 00:16:34,516
Sorry, this is kind of weird.

356
00:16:34,594 --> 00:16:37,826
No. I'm your doctor,
you can ask me anything.

357
00:16:39,532 --> 00:16:41,091
Did you have a sister?

358
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:47,773
You're Luna's brother.

359
00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:51,441
How did you know?

360
00:16:51,611 --> 00:16:53,807
Your sister gave me her heart.

361
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:57,408
My folks told me all about her.

362
00:16:57,483 --> 00:16:58,746
Her family.

363
00:16:58,818 --> 00:17:00,548
When you said your name, I...

364
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:03,681
It didn't seem, uh, fair to

